print(binary_ipv4)
```

This R function will convert the IPv4 address "128.178.163.54" to binary. It first splits the IP address into four parts, then converts each part to binary using a combination of `strsplit`, `lapply`, and `sapply`. Finally, it combines the binary parts into a single string.

