                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This code defines a main function that declares and initializes your array of integers. The main task of sorting is performed by the bubbleSort function. This function uses two nested loops to compare each pair of adjacent elements in the array and swap them if they are in the wrong order. The outer loop iterates through the array from the beginning to the end, while the inner loop iterates from the beginning to the position just before the current position. This way, each number in the array "bubbles up" to its correct position, hence the name "Bubble Sort".

Please note that Bubble Sort is not the most efficient sorting algorithm, especially for large data sets. However, it is simple and easy to understand, and it works well for this small list of integers.

